# branch.word — what a branch IS: where the chains split.
# Axiom: it bottoms out in the kernel (seed/materials/branch/ — branch.js, branchCreation.js,
# branches.js). The host tree, scope, and per-chain capture stay. Descends from word.word, base.word,
# chain.word; every word in it is grounded (branch, chain, fact, head, one, order). It names no
# `name`/`being`/`space`/`matter` — "every chain" stands for all of them, and they lean on `branch`
# from above, not the other way.

A branch is where a chain splits.
A branch splits from a fact on the branch before it, the fork.
Up to the fork the facts are shared. After the fork the branch has its own.
At the fork, every chain splits at once, each at the head it had.
Across a fork, the order is one and unbroken.
The first branch is the main. It splits from none.
